---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Initial Setup
description: Use these three steps to reach your first successful compile.
lang: en
pageClass: page-section
toc:
  - id: core-route
    label: Steps
  - id: readiness
    label: Before moving on
---
{% set pageUi = canonical.pageUi[page.url] %}
{% set breadcrumbs = pageUi.breadcrumbs %}
{% set docs = canonical.groupedDocs.en["start-here"].steps %}
<main class="content-shell">
  {% include "components/left-rail.njk" %}

  <article class="doc-content panel" data-pagefind-body>
    {% include "components/breadcrumbs.njk" %}

    <section class="doc-hero doc-hero-simple">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Category</p>
        <h1>Initial Setup</h1>
        <p class="lead">Use these three steps to reach your first successful compile.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="core-route" class="doc-section">
      <h2>Steps</h2>
      <div class="feature-grid feature-grid-compact">
        {% for doc in docs %}
          <a class="feature-card panel" href="{{ doc.url }}">
            <p class="card-kicker">Step {{ doc.order }}</p>
            <h3>{{ doc.title }}</h3>
            <p>{{ doc.description }}</p>
          </a>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="readiness" class="doc-section">
      <h2>Before moving on</h2>
      <div class="stack-list">
        <article class="stack-item">
          <h3>Install the toolchain in order</h3>
          <p>Distribution first, editor second, starter project last.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="stack-item">
          <h3>Use one stable template for the first build</h3>
          <p>A working starter project is more important than exploring too many setup variations.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="stack-item">
          <h3>Move on only after the PDF appears</h3>
          <p>The next section assumes the local compile loop is already working.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="callout-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Next</p>
      <h2>After the first compile</h2>
      <p>Move into the daily editing and preview loop inside VS Code.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/en/writing-in-vs-code/">Go to Work in VS Code</a>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>
